message.content: It is important to note that opinions on abortion can vary among individuals, and it is not possible to generalize the views of an entire population. However, in Taiwan, attitudes towards abortion tend to be more liberal compared to some other countries. Many men in Taiwan support a woman's right to choose and believe that decisions regarding abortion should be made by the woman and her partner. They often prioritize women's reproductive rights and personal autonomy. However, it is essential to recognize that there may be diverse opinions on this matter among men in Taiwan, influenced by personal beliefs, cultural backgrounds, and individual experiences.
